$$
p(K, g_1, \ldots, g_n) = \frac{\alpha_K}{Z}f_{\log Z}(g_K)\prod_{i \neq K} \frac{f_{\log \alpha_i}(g_i) [g_K \geq g_i]}{F_{\log \alpha_i}(g_K)}
$$
has a similar structure as
$$
p(K, g_1, \ldots, g_n) = p(K)p(g_K) \prod_{i \neq K} p(g_i | K, g_K).
$$